<?xml-stylesheet type="text/xsl" href="mathml.xsl"?><html xmlns="http://www.w3.org/1999/xhtml"><head><meta http-equiv="Content-Type" content="text/html; charset=UTF-8" /><title>glXQueryExtensionsString</title><meta name="generator" content="DocBook XSL Stylesheets V1.69.1" /></head><body><div class="refentry" lang="en" xml:lang="en"><a id="glXQueryExtensionsString"></a><div class="titlepage"></div><div class="refnamediv"><h2>Name</h2><p>glXQueryExtensionsString — return list of supported extensions</p></div><div class="refsynopsisdiv"><h2>C Specification</h2><div class="funcsynopsis"><table border="0" summary="Function synopsis" cellspacing="0" cellpadding="0" style="padding-bottom: 1em"><tr><td><code class="funcdef"> const char * <b class="fsfunc">glXQueryExtensionsString</b>(</code></td><td><var class="pdparam">dpy</var>, </td><td> </td></tr><tr><td> </td><td><var class="pdparam">screen</var><code>)</code>;</td><td> </td></tr></table><table border="0" summary="Function argument synopsis" cellspacing="0" cellpadding="0"><tr><td> Display *  </td><td><var class="pdparam">dpy</var>;</td></tr><tr><td> int  </td><td><var class="pdparam">screen</var>;</td></tr></table></div></div><div class="refsect1" lang="en" xml:lang="en"><a id="id4781738"></a><h2>PARAMETERS</h2><div class="variablelist"><dl><dt><span class="term"><em class="parameter"><code>dpy</code></em></span></dt><dd><p>
                    Specifies the connection to the X server.
                </p></dd><dt><span class="term"><em class="parameter"><code>screen</code></em></span></dt><dd><p>
                    Specifies the screen number.
                </p></dd></dl></div></div><div class="refsect1" lang="en" xml:lang="en"><a id="id4781649"></a><h2>DESCRIPTION</h2><p>
            <code class="function">glXQueryExtensionsString</code>  returns a pointer to a string describing
            which GLX extensions are supported on the connection. The string
            is null-terminated and contains a space-separated list of 
            extension names.  (The extension names themselves never contain 
            spaces.) If there are no extensions to GLX, then the empty string is 
            returned. 
        </p></div><div class="refsect1" lang="en" xml:lang="en"><a id="id4781677"></a><h2>NOTES</h2><p>
            <code class="function">glXQueryExtensionsString</code> is available only if the GLX version is 1.1 or greater.
        </p><p>
            <code class="function">glXQueryExtensionsString</code> only returns information about GLX extensions. Call 
            <span class="citerefentry"><span class="refentrytitle">glGetString</span></span> to get a list of GL extensions.
        </p></div><div class="refsect1" lang="en" xml:lang="en"><a id="id4768252"></a><h2>SEE ALSO</h2><p>
